Preheat oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Grease a 9x13-inch pan (non-coated). Beat together cake mix, 2 eggs, and 1/2 cup melted butter, and pour into prepared pan. In a separate bowl, mix confectioners' sugar, 2 eggs, cream cheese, and 1/2 cup melted butter. Beat well and pour on top of first layer. Bake at 375 degrees F (190 degrees C) approximately 40 minutes. Cool completely and cut into squares.